HEADWORD: Cymometer
<hw>Cy*mom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ wave
<ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument for exhibiting and
measuring wave motion</def>; <specif>specif.</specif>
<fld>(Elec.)</fld>, <def>an instrument for determining the frequency of
electric wave oscillations, esp. in connection with wireless
telegraphy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

